      • closeColumnForRemove

        public void closeColumnForRemove​(int columnIndex)
        Closed column files. Similarly to closeColumnForRemove(CharSequence) closed reader column files before column can be removed. This method takes column index usually resolved from column name by #TableReaderMetadata. Bounds checking is performed via assertion.
        Parameters:
        columnIndex - column index

      • closeColumnForRemove

        public void closeColumnForRemove​(CharSequence columnName)
        Closes column files. This method should be used before call to TableWriter.removeColumn() on Windows OS.
        Parameters:
        columnName - name of column to be closed.
